content:
I find this trick very handy once you have set it up.
In JavaScript projects Add the alias to jsconfig.json to have intellisense super powers and the advatange of absolute paths:
1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 { &#34;compilerOptions&#34;: { ... &#34;paths&#34;: { &#34;@/*&#34;: [&#34;./src/*&#34;] } ... } In TypeScript projects Install the package: @types/node as dev dependency. Import the fileURLToPath and URL 1 import { fileURLToPath, URL } from &#34;node:url&#34;; Add the resolve option in vite.config.ts : 1 2 3 4 5 resolve: { alias: { &#34;@&#34;: fileURLToPath(new URL(&#34;./src&#34;, import.meta.url)), }, }, Add the alias to tsconfig.json to avoid ESLint complaints and have intellisense super powers: 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 { &#34;compilerOptions&#34;: { ... &#34;paths&#34;: { &#34;@/*&#34;: [&#34;./src/*&#34;] } ... }
